1
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:04,041
[ Insects buzzing ]

2
00:00:04,125 --> 00:00:06,166
[ "Nocturne in D-flat Major,
Opus 27, Number 2" playing ]

3
00:00:06,250 --> 00:00:13,375
♪♪

4
00:00:13,458 --> 00:00:22,500
♪♪

5
00:00:22,583 --> 00:00:30,708
♪♪

6
00:00:30,791 --> 00:00:39,000
♪♪

7
00:00:39,083 --> 00:00:41,291
Kousei:<i> I thought if I came</i>
<i>to the music room,</i>

8
00:00:41,375 --> 00:00:43,958
<i>you'd be there like always,</i>

9
00:00:44,041 --> 00:00:45,291
<i>but you're nowhere to be found.</i>

10
00:00:45,375 --> 00:00:49,833
<i>I don't know your phone number</i>
<i>or e-mail.</i>

11
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:52,208
<i>I guess...</i>

12
00:00:52,291 --> 00:00:56,291
<i>I don't really know</i>
<i>anything about you.</i>

13
00:00:56,375 --> 00:00:57,916
Kousei, there you are!
[ Yelps ]

14
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:00,541
It's about Kaori.

15
00:01:00,625 --> 00:01:02,833
She --
She collapsed again.

16
00:01:02,916 --> 00:01:04,791
[ Panting ]

17
00:01:04,875 --> 00:01:11,541
♪♪

18
00:01:11,625 --> 00:01:13,333
[ Kousei panting ]

19
00:01:15,791 --> 00:01:16,666
[ Gasps ]

20
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:19,208
Hey!
Good to see you!

21
00:01:19,291 --> 00:01:21,041
I wanted to let you know
what's up,

22
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:22,833
but I was kind of
out of commission.

23
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:25,833
I just figured
you'd back out without me.

24
00:01:26,666 --> 00:01:29,750
Sorry I flaked on you.

25
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:31,791
[ "Nanairo Symphony" playing ]

26
00:01:31,875 --> 00:01:34,791
♪♪

27
00:01:34,875 --> 00:01:38,583
[ Singing in Japanese ]

28
00:01:38,666 --> 00:01:47,583
♪♪

29
00:01:47,666 --> 00:01:56,625
♪♪

30
00:01:56,708 --> 00:02:05,625
♪♪

31
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:14,666
♪♪

32
00:02:14,750 --> 00:02:23,750
♪♪

33
00:02:23,833 --> 00:02:32,750
♪♪

34
00:02:32,833 --> 00:02:41,750
♪♪

35
00:02:41,833 --> 00:02:50,833
♪♪

36
00:02:50,916 --> 00:02:59,833
♪♪

37
00:02:59,916 --> 00:03:02,791
[ Insects buzzing ]

38
00:03:02,875 --> 00:03:04,583
Tsubaki:
So, what'd you get her?

39
00:03:04,666 --> 00:03:05,666
Watari:
Cake from Yoshitomo.

40
00:03:05,750 --> 00:03:07,625
Girls have a sweet tooth.

41
00:03:07,708 --> 00:03:10,375
Kousei: Her family
runs a bakery, Einstein.

42
00:03:10,458 --> 00:03:13,500
Oh. A for effort,
though, right?

43
00:03:13,583 --> 00:03:15,250
Ta-da!

44
00:03:16,666 --> 00:03:18,875
Welcome back.

45
00:03:18,958 --> 00:03:20,708
Hope you're
in the mood to pig out.

46
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:22,083
That's for me?
[ Gasps ]

47
00:03:22,166 --> 00:03:23,500
So how you feeling?

48
00:03:23,583 --> 00:03:24,791
Full of vim and vigor.

49
00:03:24,875 --> 00:03:26,541
They just want to run
a couple tests.

50
00:03:26,625 --> 00:03:28,791
I bet you fainted
'cause you miss me so bad.

51
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:30,875
[ Giggles ]
"Paging Dr. Watari."

52
00:03:30,958 --> 00:03:33,416
Kousei:
<i>It's happened twice now.</i>

53
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,625
Didn't they run tests
on you last time, too?

54
00:03:35,708 --> 00:03:36,750
Well, yeah, but they
want to be thorough.

55
00:03:36,833 --> 00:03:39,208
You know how doctors are.

56
00:03:39,291 --> 00:03:41,166
I did hit my head.

57
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:43,375
They want to make sure
this performance of mine

58
00:03:43,458 --> 00:03:44,958
doesn't get an encore.

59
00:03:45,041 --> 00:03:47,708
What's the big deal with
those wandering eyes, Friend
A?!

60
00:03:47,791 --> 00:03:49,458
Or is it Friend T&A?!

61
00:03:49,541 --> 00:03:51,500
Just look at you
drooling over me!

62
00:03:51,583 --> 00:03:53,291
I swear I'm not
drooling over you!

63
00:03:53,375 --> 00:03:54,708
I swear that I am!

64
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:57,375
It really threw us
for a loop.

65
00:03:57,458 --> 00:04:00,000
No-show at the gala,
and then you're in here.

66
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:01,875
You're thrown?
Think of what I went through.

67
00:04:01,958 --> 00:04:03,708
All I did
was bonk my head a little.

68
00:04:03,791 --> 00:04:04,708
[ Wails ]

69
00:04:04,791 --> 00:04:05,791
Blood everywhere,

70
00:04:05,875 --> 00:04:08,500
gushing out like a hose!

71
00:04:08,583 --> 00:04:09,583
It was like
a horror movie!

72
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:12,125
Anyway, my parents
totally freaked out

73
00:04:12,208 --> 00:04:13,625
and took me
straight to the hospital.

74
00:04:13,708 --> 00:04:14,375
The end.

75
00:04:14,458 --> 00:04:15,750
Ooh!
Is that a tart?

76
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:17,083
I call dibs.

77
00:04:17,166 --> 00:04:19,291
I have always
gotten tired easily.

78
00:04:19,375 --> 00:04:22,500
Guess I pushed myself
a little too hard lately.

79
00:04:22,583 --> 00:04:23,666
Got to learn to chill out.

80
00:04:24,875 --> 00:04:26,750
Mmm!

81
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:29,250
<i>She can't even</i>
<i>chill out about dessert.</i>

82
00:04:29,333 --> 00:04:30,250
Brought you some books,
too!

83
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:32,416
Time to kiss
your boredom goodbye!

84
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:33,958
Huh?! These are all
from the library.

85
00:04:34,041 --> 00:04:36,458
Did you even
check them out?

86
00:04:36,541 --> 00:04:38,041
No, but too late
for that now.

87
00:04:38,125 --> 00:04:38,916
Your heart was
in the right place,

88
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,375
but isn't this
overkill?

89
00:04:41,458 --> 00:04:43,416
How you figure?
Think about it.

90
00:04:43,500 --> 00:04:46,083
Kaori's not gonna be away from
school for that long, right?

91
00:04:46,166 --> 00:04:47,791
Mm-hmm,
not long at all.

92
00:04:47,875 --> 00:04:49,416
-You see? That's what...
-Kousei:<i> When she said that,</i>

93
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:51,916
<i>why'd it feel like...</i>
-...too many books.

94
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:54,625
<i>...she's practiced that reply</i>
<i>a few times?</i>

95
00:04:54,708 --> 00:04:57,750
Watari: We got to go,
but I'll see you in my dreams.

96
00:04:57,833 --> 00:04:59,375
Tsubaki:
Dumbass. Later!

97
00:04:59,458 --> 00:05:00,250
Thanks, you guys!

98
00:05:05,458 --> 00:05:07,291
No way I'm gonna get
through this pile.

99
00:05:13,541 --> 00:05:14,625
[ Gasps ]

100
00:05:17,125 --> 00:05:18,166
[ Chuckles ]

101
00:05:18,250 --> 00:05:20,166
[ Door opens ]

102
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:22,125
Hey, Kaori.
Yeah?

103
00:05:22,208 --> 00:05:23,625
Did your friends
call it a day?

104
00:05:23,708 --> 00:05:24,291
Yeah.

105
00:05:24,375 --> 00:05:26,458
Back to it, then?

106
00:05:26,541 --> 00:05:27,708
Guess so.

107
00:05:27,791 --> 00:05:31,416
Go ahead and hook me up
to the I.V. drip again.

108
00:05:35,166 --> 00:05:37,791
[ Cellphone rings ]
Tsubaki: Oh.

109
00:05:37,875 --> 00:05:40,375
Kashiwagi: You get a text?
It's Saito.

110
00:05:40,458 --> 00:05:42,583
He says we should go
to the festival later.

111
00:05:42,666 --> 00:05:44,791
Sounds a lot
like a date, Tsubaki.

112
00:05:44,875 --> 00:05:46,750
Haven't you broken up
with him yet?

113
00:05:46,833 --> 00:05:48,291
Why would I do that?
Why not?

114
00:05:50,375 --> 00:05:52,166
What do you mean?

115
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:54,500
It's not like
I don't like the guy.

116
00:05:54,583 --> 00:05:56,166
Do you like him?

117
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:57,708
Well, duh.

118
00:05:58,916 --> 00:05:59,875
I've had a crush
on him forever.

119
00:05:59,958 --> 00:06:03,500
So what's with Arima?

120
00:06:03,583 --> 00:06:04,833
[ Sighs ]

121
00:06:04,916 --> 00:06:06,666
Kousei:<i> Tsubaki?</i>

122
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:08,500
<i>Tsubaki.</i>

123
00:06:08,583 --> 00:06:10,041
He's -- Wow!

124
00:06:10,125 --> 00:06:12,500
Bringing up Kousei
when we're talking about Saito?

125
00:06:12,583 --> 00:06:15,500
[ Laughs ]
You're so random, ain't ya?

126
00:06:15,583 --> 00:06:17,583
Kousei's just...

127
00:06:17,666 --> 00:06:19,958
We've been joined at the hip
ever since we were kids.

128
00:06:20,041 --> 00:06:22,208
He's not like
a guy to me.

129
00:06:22,291 --> 00:06:25,791
I see him as
a little brother.

130
00:06:25,875 --> 00:06:28,375
I'm not sure that you do.
[ Gasps ]

131
00:06:28,458 --> 00:06:30,208
But you think
if you say it enough times,

132
00:06:30,291 --> 00:06:33,666
you'll convince everyone,
including yourself.

133
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:35,541
You're too chicken
to face the facts,

134
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:37,083
'cause maybe it ruins
the safe thing

135
00:06:37,166 --> 00:06:39,791
you've got going
right now.

136
00:06:43,125 --> 00:06:45,541
[ Grunting ]
[ Gasps ]

137
00:06:45,625 --> 00:06:46,500
[ Growling ]

138
00:06:46,583 --> 00:06:47,791
The egg
is my favorite.

139
00:06:47,875 --> 00:06:49,541
I was saving it
for last.

140
00:06:49,625 --> 00:06:52,041
He's like a little brother.
That's all!

141
00:06:52,125 --> 00:06:53,708
<i>Well, that sure</i>
<i>didn't do the trick.</i>

142
00:06:53,791 --> 00:06:54,875
That's all!

143
00:06:54,958 --> 00:06:57,666
<i>Arima was afraid, too,</i>

144
00:06:57,750 --> 00:06:58,583
<i>but he took the plunge.</i>

145
00:06:58,666 --> 00:07:00,250
Do what you want,
chicken,

146
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:03,375
but you got to
cross that road someday.

147
00:07:06,166 --> 00:07:08,125
[ Indistinct conversations ]

148
00:07:08,208 --> 00:07:15,750
♪♪

149
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:18,125
Hey, a yukata.

150
00:07:18,208 --> 00:07:20,041
It looks good on you.

151
00:07:20,125 --> 00:07:22,416
You're cute.
I mean it.

152
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,750
[ Giggles ]
It's just the same old me

153
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:25,666
dressed up
for a change.

154
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:27,125
It's all about
the yukata.

155
00:07:27,208 --> 00:07:29,791
<i>He told me I'm cute.</i>

156
00:07:29,875 --> 00:07:32,125
<i>Kousei would never</i>
<i>say that to me,</i>

157
00:07:32,208 --> 00:07:33,750
<i>'cause</i>
<i>when he looks at me,</i>

158
00:07:33,833 --> 00:07:37,750
<i>all he sees is the big sis</i>
<i>who bosses him around.</i>

159
00:07:38,416 --> 00:07:40,041
<i>I'm sure of it.</i>

160
00:07:41,125 --> 00:07:42,291
<i>I can tell.</i>

161
00:07:44,041 --> 00:07:45,791
Kaori: The festival's
tonight, isn't it?

162
00:07:45,875 --> 00:07:47,000
Yeah.

163
00:07:47,083 --> 00:07:48,458
At ease, soldier.

164
00:07:48,541 --> 00:07:49,125
Have a seat.

165
00:07:49,208 --> 00:07:51,166
I could, I guess,

166
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:53,875
but I think I'll stand.

167
00:07:53,958 --> 00:07:56,208
What you think I'm gonna do,
put a tack on it?

168
00:07:56,291 --> 00:07:59,791
I don't like hospitals
much.

169
00:07:59,875 --> 00:08:01,125
<i>You'll be okay, right?</i>

170
00:08:01,208 --> 00:08:03,666
<i>Those tests'll</i>
<i>come back fine,</i>

171
00:08:03,750 --> 00:08:06,833
<i>and you'll be back at school</i>
<i>any day now.</i>

172
00:08:06,916 --> 00:08:09,666
<i>We'll hang out</i>
<i>in the music room like before,</i>

173
00:08:09,750 --> 00:08:12,750
<i>just the two of us,</i>
<i>won't we?</i>

174
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,750
Are you gonna --
Hey, guess what.

175
00:08:14,833 --> 00:08:16,791
Watari was just here.

176
00:08:16,875 --> 00:08:17,666
He brought me a snack.

177
00:08:17,750 --> 00:08:19,291
<i>Watari.</i>
We talked for a bit,

178
00:08:19,375 --> 00:08:22,916
mostly about
your one-man "Liebesleid."

179
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,666
You forgot to mention it,
you know.

180
00:08:24,750 --> 00:08:26,000
Uh, yeah.

181
00:08:26,083 --> 00:08:28,541
The accompanist playing
a duet all by himself!

182
00:08:28,625 --> 00:08:30,125
What kind of a showoff
does that?!

183
00:08:30,208 --> 00:08:31,708
I mean, it was a violin
concert,
but whatever, right?

184
00:08:31,791 --> 00:08:35,166
Good job, Friend A. Way to
totally confuse the audience.

185
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:37,500
It's your fault I had to
in the first place!

186
00:08:37,583 --> 00:08:39,166
What do you mean?

187
00:08:39,250 --> 00:08:40,333
When I didn't show up,

188
00:08:40,416 --> 00:08:43,000
I thought you would
just go home.

189
00:08:44,291 --> 00:08:45,166
I was gonna,

190
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:48,208
but this boy
insulted you.

191
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:51,041
Like always,
the notes disappeared on me.

192
00:08:51,125 --> 00:08:55,000
Just when all was lost,

193
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:57,000
I thought of my mom.

194
00:08:57,083 --> 00:08:58,541
My memories of her,

195
00:08:58,625 --> 00:09:01,541
they turned into notes
and filled the hall.

196
00:09:01,625 --> 00:09:03,750
See?
[ Gasps ]

197
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:06,041
You're a musician,
no matter what,

198
00:09:06,125 --> 00:09:08,541
aren't you,
Kousei Arima?

199
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:12,500
<i>Yeah, I was right.</i>

200
00:09:12,583 --> 00:09:14,458
<i>"Love's Sorrow,"</i>

201
00:09:14,541 --> 00:09:15,583
<i>she chose it because of me.</i>

202
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:18,875
<i>Whenever I hear it,</i>

203
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:22,833
<i>my thoughts always drift</i>
<i>to my mother.</i>

204
00:09:24,208 --> 00:09:26,708
<i>The scent of clothes</i>
<i>in the sun.</i>

205
00:09:26,791 --> 00:09:29,875
<i>The sound of the piano</i>
<i>all around me.</i>

206
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:31,416
<i>A quiet lullaby.</i>

207
00:09:31,500 --> 00:09:33,875
<i>The smell of antiseptic.</i>

208
00:09:33,958 --> 00:09:37,208
<i>Echoing footsteps.</i>

209
00:09:37,291 --> 00:09:39,791
<i>A linoleum floor,</i>
<i>well worn.</i>

210
00:09:39,875 --> 00:09:41,750
<i>I can't forget them.</i>

211
00:09:41,833 --> 00:09:42,916
Welcome back.

212
00:09:44,291 --> 00:09:47,916
Your "Love's Sorrow,"
I wish I could have heard it.

213
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:49,791
<i>You're okay, right?</i>

214
00:09:49,875 --> 00:09:52,750
I wish I could have
played with you again.

215
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,583
<i>Tell me you're okay,</i>

216
00:09:54,666 --> 00:09:57,250
<i>that the tests</i>
<i>are for nothing.</i>

217
00:09:57,333 --> 00:10:00,083
<i>Tell me that you're</i>
<i>coming back to school.</i>

218
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:04,208
<i>You are, right?</i>

219
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:06,750
That's twice now.

220
00:10:06,833 --> 00:10:07,291
Huh?

221
00:10:07,375 --> 00:10:09,666
Just now...

222
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:11,708
you called me
by my name.

223
00:10:13,208 --> 00:10:15,750
<i>Kaori...</i>

224
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:17,958
<i>you're not going</i>
<i>to leave me, are you...</i>

225
00:10:19,625 --> 00:10:20,791
<i>like my mother did?</i>

226
00:10:24,833 --> 00:10:27,833
Welcome to the Sumiya Baseball
Youth Sports boot camp!

227
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:30,166
I'm gonna make sluggers
out of every last one of you!

228
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:32,791
[ Boys clamoring ]

229
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:34,333
Just for that,
10 sets of wind sprints

230
00:10:34,416 --> 00:10:36,916
along the water!
Now move it!

231
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:37,666
[ Boys groaning ]

232
00:10:39,958 --> 00:10:41,958
But I don't play baseball,
Tsubaki. Can I go?

233
00:10:42,041 --> 00:10:45,666
What do you press those piano
pedals with, huh?! Your feet!

234
00:10:45,750 --> 00:10:48,583
Hey, they're not that hard
to press, I swear!

235
00:10:48,666 --> 00:10:51,000
Check out
those tiny, little prints.

236
00:10:51,083 --> 00:10:52,166
They're not tiny!
They just look that way,

237
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:53,166
'cause you're Bigfoot!

238
00:10:53,250 --> 00:10:54,708
What did you call me?!

239
00:10:54,791 --> 00:10:57,791
I'm gonna use these big feet
to kick your butt!

240
00:10:57,875 --> 00:10:59,041
-[ Wails ]
-Come back here, you!

241
00:10:59,125 --> 00:11:01,041
[ Yells ]

242
00:11:04,708 --> 00:11:07,750
Hey, Kousei,
want to go to the park with me?

243
00:11:07,833 --> 00:11:08,833
I wish I could,

244
00:11:08,916 --> 00:11:12,125
but I got to get home
for my piano lesson.

245
00:11:12,208 --> 00:11:13,708
Hmph. I just
wanted to show him

246
00:11:13,791 --> 00:11:16,291
this mud ball
I've been working on.

247
00:11:16,375 --> 00:11:18,041
It's as shiny
as a marble.

248
00:11:18,125 --> 00:11:20,541
This here is
a fine-looking specimen.

249
00:11:20,625 --> 00:11:22,666
I should go pro.

250
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:23,708
I know.

251
